##############ARCHIVE################

tar

c – Create an archive from a file or directory
x – Extract archive
r – Append file to archive
t - List the contents of the archive


Create tar file of directory.
$ tar -cf archive.tar some_dir/

Create tar file of multiple files.

$ tar -cf archive.tar file1.txt file2.txt

Extract.

$ tar -xf archive.tar 

Extract to specific folder.

$ tar -xf archive.tar -C /home/a/Downloads/

Extract a particular type of file.

$ tar -xf archive.tar --wildcards "*.png"

Append files to existing archives.

$ tar -rf archive.tar file.txt

List files in archive.

$ tar -tvf archive.tar 


*$ cpio*
#################COMPRESS######################

Compress file.

$ gzip archive.tar

*Creates file archive.tar.gz*

OR

$ zip myfiles.zip file1 file2

$ unzip myfile.zip

################ARCHIVE AND COMPRESS##############

Create compressed archive.

$ tar -czf archive.tgz file1.txt file2.txt
 
Extract compressed archive.

$ tar -xzf archive.tgz
